# Java/Spring Boot Clean Architecture Service

## <%= serviceNamePascal %>

A production-ready microservice built with Spring Boot 3.4+ following Clean Architecture principles.

## Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- JDK 21+
- Maven 3.9+
- PostgreSQL 14+
- Docker (optional, for Testcontainers)

### Running Locally

```bash
# Build
./mvnw clean install

# Run application
./mvnw spring-boot:run

# Run tests
./mvnw test
```

### Access Points
- **Application**: http://localhost:8080
- **Swagger UI**: http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html
- **Actuator Health**: http://localhost:8080/actuator/health

## Architecture

This service follows Clean Architecture with four layers:

```
src/main/java/<packageName>/
├── domain/           # Enterprise business rules (pure Java, no frameworks)
│   ├── models/       # Entities, value objects
│   ├── ports/        # Repository interfaces, event publishers
│   └── services/     # Domain services
├── application/      # Application business rules
│   ├── usecases/    # Use case interfaces + implementations
│   ├── dtos/        # Data transfer objects
│   └── sagas/       # Saga orchestrators
├── infrastructure/   # Framework implementations
│   ├── api/         # REST controllers
│   ├── persistence/ # JPA repositories, entities
│   ├── config/      # Spring configuration
│   └── events/      # Event publishers
└── presentation/    # HTTP layer
    └── api/         # API routers
```

