## Development

### Adding a New Feature

Use the Yeoman generator:

```bash
yo clean-architecture:endpoint
```

Or follow SOP-02: [Add REST Endpoint](../../docs/04-sops/02-add-new-rest-endpoint.md)

### Running Architecture Validation

```bash
./mvnw test -Dtest=*ArchTest
```

## Deployment

### Docker

```bash
docker build -t <%= serviceNameKebab %> .
docker run -p 8080:8080 -e DATABASE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://host:5432/db <%= serviceNameKebab %>
```

### Environment Variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `DATABASE_URL` | `jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/<%= serviceNameKebab %>` | PostgreSQL connection |
| `DATABASE_USER` | `postgres` | Database username |
| `DATABASE_PASSWORD` | `postgres` | Database password |
| `SERVER_PORT` | `8080` | HTTP port |

## Testing

```bash
# All tests
./mvnw test

# Unit tests only
./mvnw test -Dtest=*Test

# Integration tests
./mvnw test -Dtest=*IntegrationTest

# Architecture tests
./mvnw test -Dtest=*ArchTest
```

